VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT new SqlCommand\(.*\)
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:(\+|String\.Format|Request\.|QueryString|Form) && MISSING:(SqlParameter|AddWithValue|Parameters\.Add|Parameters\.AddWithValue)
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the usage of SqlCommand without parameterized queries, which can lead to SQL injection vulnerabilities.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Untrusted Input Handling in SQL Query: SqlCommand.
